 1990-13641990-06-280,  ,  ,  ,  ,  OLD INAC,  , 
PrecisAcceptance of an instrument intitled "Document of Absolute Surrender" which was assented to by the STANGECOMING BAND OF OJIBWAY at a referendum held on April 12, 1990, whereby all rights, title and interest of whatsoever kind that the band may have in some 1,863 hectares of land formerly known as Rainy Lake Indian Reserve No. 18B, situate in the District of Rainy River, in the Province of Ontario, will be surrendered unto the Crown.
